main event: An oblong silver object was observed moving east and ascending over Gulliver, Michigan, for approximately 5:30 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 5:30 minutes., The object was described as having no wings, fins, or appendages., The object was estimated to be significant in size but the exact dimensions were not specified., The observation was made by a civilian source, specifically a mother and daughter., The conclusion of the report indicated that the object was possibly astronomical in nature.
